<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900411-0058</DOCNO><DOCID>900411-0058.</DOCID><HL>   Bank of New England Sale</HL><DATE>04/11/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2</SO><CO>   NEB T.NA</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)BANKS (BNK)</IN><LP>   BOSTON -- Bank of New England Corp. said it signed adefinitive agreement to sell its asset-based lendingsubsidiary, New England Commercial Finance Corp., to NationalBank of Canada.   Included in the sale are about $665 million in assets,which were sold at a premium, Bank of New England said. Theamount of the premium -- the difference between the salesprice and the assets' book value -- wasn't disclosed.</LP><TEXT>   National Bank said the assets represent loans to about 125borrowers. It said that less than 5% of the assets includedare loans for leveraged transactions and that none arereal-estate loans.   The sale, expected to close by the end of April, is partof Bank of New England's previously announced asset-salesprogram. Proceeds of the sales are being used to reduce thecompany's liquidity problems and to improve its capitalratios.   National Bank of Canada, based in Montreal, has assets of35.9 billion Canadian dollars (US$30.9 billion). Bank of NewEngland has assets of about $25 billion.</TEXT></DOC>